Description:
A cross-river CSO Platform on Human Rights advocacy and action is established.
At least 25 CSOs, members of the platform receive training on human rights standards, incl monitoring, and receive coaching on joint advocacy actions to promote peace and social cohesion.                            
At least 30 members of 3 regional advocacy groups of persons with disabilities, OPDS have strenghtened capacities to claim their rights and meaningfully participate in public and civil life and decision making process;

Increased participation of young men and women in community proceses in line with international standards and Agenda 2030 by ensuring that sex-disaggregated and age-disaggregated evidence are gathered, data-base on youth participation standard developed, capacity building of  youth workers for the newly addopted NYS implementation completed.
Increased  participation through UNICEF U-Report platform with more voices of adolescent girls and boys comming from rural areas having their voices heard. 
mechanisms to improve the quality, accessibility and relevance of volunteering programmes are strengthened.
TA to Ministries and bodies at the national and local levels provided to support changes in the area of practical policies and regulatory frameworks, ensuring participation of Youth Advisory bodies and young people in consultation processes and advocacy for strategic priorities and public policies related to the overall wellbeing of children and adolescents, on local and national level, including climate change; 
- Technical support provided to the Ministry of  Tourism and Youth on the Law on Youth;
- Professional, technical and organizational support provided for the needs of the Working Group of the Ministry of Labor, Employment, Veterans and Social Affairs on Amendments to the Law on Volunteering and Internship

